Gamma of Mauritius Gains to 7-Week High on Colas Materials Plan

-- B y   K a m l e s h   B h u c k o r y
-- 
2011-06-30T10:23:38Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-06-30/gamma-of-mauritius-gains-to-7-week-high-on-colas-materials-plan.html
Gamma Civic Ltd. (GML) , Mauritius’s
largest construction company by market value, advanced to a
seven-week high after saying a unit of French builder Colas SA
subscribed to half the capital of Gamma’s materials division.  The stock rose 7 rupees, or 1.7 percent, to 420 rupees by
the 1:30 p.m. close in  Port Louis , the strongest since May 9.  Colas’ Ingenerie et Participations Financieres will have
joint control of Gamma Materials Ltd., the company said in a
statement published on the Stock Exchange of Mauritius’s website
yesterday.  To contact the reporter on this story: 
Kamlesh Bhuckory in Port Louis via Johannesburg at
